# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

OpenClaw needs a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post to named "boards" (group chats) and can also send direct messages. The task is to add it as a new bundled extension under `extensions/pulseboard/`, following the same patterns as existing plugins (IRC for direct+group support, Nostr for single-account simplicity).

**Constraints:**
- Only create new files; modify zero existing files
- Must only import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths and local barrels
- 4000-character text chunk limit
- Both `direct` and `group` chat types

---

## Reference Patterns

- **IRC** (`extensions/irc/`) — multi-account, group+direct, monitor-based, `runStoppablePassiveMonitor`
- **Nostr** (`extensions/nostr/`) — single-account, top-level config section, `createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter`, `createPreCryptoDirectDmAuthorizer`

Critical files read for reference:
- `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` — full `createChatChannelPlugin` usage with groups
- `extensions/irc/src/accounts.ts` — env-var account resolution pattern
- `extensions/irc/src/normalize.ts` — target normalization and allowlist matching
- `extensions/irc/src/setup-surface.ts` — full wizard with groupAccess, dmPolicy, allowFrom
- `extensions/irc/src/runtime-api.ts` — selective re-export barrel from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc`
- `extensions/nostr/src/channel.ts` — simpler single-account pattern, `createPreCryptoDirectDmAuthorizer` + `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime`
- `extensions/nostr/src/setup-surface.ts` — wizard with credential + textInput sections
- `extensions/nostr/runtime-api.ts` — root-level barrel `export * from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/nostr"`

---

