# PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan

## Context

OpenClaw needs a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post to named "boards" (group chats) and can also send direct messages. The task is to add it as a new bundled extension under `extensions/pulseboard/`, following the same patterns as existing plugins (IRC for direct+group support, Nostr for single-account simplicity).

**Constraints:**
- Only create new files; modify zero existing files
- Must only import from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` subpaths and local barrels
- 4000-character text chunk limit
- Both `direct` and `group` chat types

---

